      "side": 1,
      "message": "There is a bit of overlap with af_xdp_device_input_drain_rxq(): both walk AF_XDP descriptors, convert UMEM addresses to buffer indices, batch them, and free them. I would keep the RX-ring and fill-ring mechanics separate because the ownership/release rules differ, but maybe factor the small addr-to-bi/batched-free pattern into a helper. That would also make it harder to accidentally use vlib_buffer_free() here while the RX drain path uses vlib_buffer_free_no_next().",
      "revId": "329d1515e2244fd39d310398cf5e4f34d483a1f2",
      "serverId": "6d2eb258-4fe2-443e-8a38-ca81da23d4c2"
    },
    {
