      "writtenOn": "2026-06-29T12:51:29Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I think this should use vlib_buffer_free_no_next(). The buffers in the fill queue were allocated and handed to AF_XDP, but they are not reinitialized with the af_xdp buffer template until RX consumes them. If one of those buffers still has stale VLIB_BUFFER_NEXT_PRESENT/next_buffer from a previous use, vlib_buffer_free() can follow that stale chain during interface delete and free unrelated buffers. The RX drain path already uses vlib_buffer_free_no_next() for this kind of raw descriptor buffer cleanup.",
      "revId": "329d1515e2244fd39d310398cf5e4f34d483a1f2",
      "serverId": "6d2eb258-4fe2-443e-8a38-ca81da23d4c2"
    },
