      "message": "This looks like a good candidate for a single constant-folded helper. af_xdp_device_output_free() and af_xdp_device_output_free_mb() have the same completion-ring walk; the semantic difference is only the final free operation: vlib_buffer_free() for single-buffer completions, vlib_buffer_free_no_next() for multi-buffer descriptor completions. Could we use one static_always_inline function with a const int is_mb parameter here?",
